{
  "text": "with the lme4 package [CITATION_1] . The R analysis code can be viewed at https://github.com/frankgarcea/GarceaStollBuxbaum. There were three main effects in our analysis: Group (LCVA participants, neurotypical participants), Neighbor Type (action, function, unrelated) and Congruence (congruent, incongruent). Prior to running each model, we assessed if there was an effect of the order of block presentation; we also included random intercepts for subject and item. All mixed-effect models were assessed by mapping the log likelihood ratio of a full and reduced model using a chi square distribution. We removed interaction terms and assessed the full model when testing for significant main effects. An alpha threshold of 0.05 was used to determine statistical significance, and all effects are reported as log odds.",
